sequenceDiagram
  %% Diagram 07: CQRS Write Path - Command Handler to Event Store

  autonumber
  actor U as Client
  participant G as API Gateway
  participant I as Idempotency Store
  participant B as Command Bus
  participant H as Command Handler
  participant DB as PostgreSQL Primary
  participant ES as Event Store
  participant R as Redis PubSub/Queue
  participant O as Observability

  U->>G: HTTPS Command Request + idempotency key
  G->>I: Check idempotency key
  alt Duplicate command key
    I-->>G: Existing command outcome
    G-->>U: Replay-safe prior response
  else New command key
    G->>B: Authenticated command dispatch
    B->>H: Execute command

    H->>H: Validate authorization + business rules
    alt Validation failed
      H-->>B: Reject command (domain error)
      B-->>G: 4xx response + correlation ID
      G-->>U: Failure response
    else Validation passed
      H->>DB: Begin transaction + write state changes
      alt DB write failed
        DB-->>H: Write error
        H-->>B: Transaction rolled back
        H->>O: Emit technical failure log
        B-->>G: Failure response + correlation ID
        G-->>U: Failure response
      else DB write succeeded
        H->>ES: Append event (aggregate_id, type, version, payload)
        alt Event append failed
          ES-->>H: Append error
          H->>DB: Rollback transaction (atomicity)
          H->>O: Emit critical append failure log
          H-->>B: Command failed, no state committed
          B-->>G: Failure response + correlation ID
          G-->>U: Failure response
        else Event append succeeded
          H->>R: Publish event for projectors/side effects
          H-->>B: Command success + aggregate version
          B-->>G: 2xx response + correlation ID
          G-->>U: Success response
        end
      end
    end
  end
